  <title translate="true">How to Filter the Tasks</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">How to Filter the Tasks</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:#ffffff;" translate="true">So as to streamline the tasks in the list and sort out the unnecessary ones, you and your users require a set of predefined filters for tasks. Filter for tasks can be created using several methods. Generally, one may go to the page of filters through the menu item</text><text styleclass="apple-converted-space" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:#ffffff; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:#ffffff;" translate="true">Tasks Management » Filters List</text><text styleclass="apple-converted-space" style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:#ffffff; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Verdana; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:#ffffff;" translate="true">. You will notice that the filters are connected to the project and apply to the sub-tasks of the project downwards in the hierarchy. This means that the filters, created for the root task, will be visible in all the projects of TrackStudio.</text></para>
